annotationA: Cell division cycle 27 is a component of the anaphase-promoting complex/cyclosome (APC/C). It is important for substrate recruitment and interacts with its co-activators, fzy and rap, as well as the mitotic checkpoint proteins, mad2 and BubR1
annotationB: Putative APC11 anaphase-promoting complex subunit; Zinc ion binding; mitotic anaphase-promoting complex activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: positive regulation of mitotic metaphase/anaphase transition; protein ubiquitination; anaphase-promoting complex-dependent proteasomal ubiquitin-dependent protein catabolic process
